TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {66103=4391 runs after 35, and 2354 outside top five, 49055=Tom Taylor, a product of the Derbyshire academy, signed his first professional contract in 2014. He made his first-class debut in Derbyshire's first victory of the Championship season, when they defeated Leicestershire in June. Although a specialist bowler, it was with the bat where he made most impact, scoring 40 during an important partnership with centurion David Wainwright to help his side to victory., 49569=His maiden first-class wicket came in his next game against Surrey when he dismissed the South African batsman Hashim Amla. He took his first five-wicket haul - at only 19 - when he returned figures of 5 for 58 as Derbyshire beat Gloucestershire at the Cheltenham Festival. Injury at the start of August which ruled him out for the remainder of the 2014 season., 34273=Born December 21, 1994, Stoke-on-Trent, Staffordshire, 51990=Jul 27, 2014}
